1.Given an array arr[]. The task is to find the number of odd and even elements in the array.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public static void countOddEven(Integer arr[]) {
 
        int countOdd = 0, countEven = 0;
        int n = arr.length;
 
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (arr[i] % 2 == 0) {
                countEven++;
            } else
                countOdd++;
        }
        System.out.println(countOdd + " " + countEven);
    }
}
